# HWSETA Grid Style

- For new grids and tables, use the shared HWSETA table look instead of introducing a new visual pattern.
- Prefer a wrapper such as `overflow-x-auto rounded-xl border border-slate-100`.
- Prefer table classes such as `min-w-full divide-y divide-slate-200 text-left text-sm`.
- Use a green header row with classes aligned to existing admin grids, for example `bg-hwseta-green text-xs font-semibold uppercase text-white shadow-sm`.
- Use `tbody` with `divide-y divide-slate-100 bg-white`.
- Keep row hover states subtle and consistent, for example `hover:bg-emerald-50/30`.
- Use compact cell spacing similar to existing site grids, typically `px-3 py-2.5` or `px-3 py-3`.
- Avoid adding long helper paragraphs above or below grids unless the user explicitly asks for instructional copy.
- Keep action cells compact and aligned right when they contain buttons.
- When a new screen needs a grid, match existing HWSETA admin grid styling first, then extend only if the feature truly needs something different.
